# Summary
This documentation details performance metrics and caching mechanisms for Amplitude Experiment's evaluation modes (local and remote), explaining how CDN caching affects response times, with remote evaluation showing 35.9ms average for cache hits versus 194.21ms for misses globally, while local evaluation performs at sub-millisecond speeds across Node.js, Go, and JVM SDKs.

